Django provide direct cookie manipulation methods on the request and response objects (so you don&rsquo;t need a helper function).
Setting a cookie:
def view(request): response = HttpResponse(&#39;blah&#39;) response.set_cookie(&#39;cookie_name&#39;, &#39;cookie_value&#39;) Retrieving a cookie:
def view(request): value = request.COOKIES.get(&#39;cookie_name&#39;) if value is None: # Cookie is not set # OR try: value = request.COOKIES[&#39;cookie_name&#39;] except KeyError:

